That's enough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 705<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/03 10:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Labeling &quot;Evil&quot; and &quot;Good&quot;</span><hr size=1> One time I was invited by a friend to participate in a Sebilis group.  I had never been, so I was prett excited.  My friend then said &quot;bring Vivienne along.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, I asked Vivienne if she wanted to go, and she said yes.  Then on the way to meet up with the group, I was informed by my friend that there was a paladin in the group who refuses to group with dark elves.  So I told my friend I was sorry, but I refuse to group with someone who won't group with dark elves.  It was another couple of months before I ever entered Sebilis.  But I have no regrets.<br>
<br>
Is the paladin wrong for wanting to maintain his roleplay?  Am I wrong for maintaining mine?  I don't think so.<br>
<br>
Another time, I died in Nadox.  A monk in another group brought my corpse to me and then suddenly remembered that there was a cleric in his group.  The cleric came over, saw who I was grouped with and asked me &quot;You group with dark elves?&quot;  I said &quot;I am married to a dark elf.&quot;<br>
<br>
The cleric then walked away.  &quot;I refuse to aid anyone that works with dark elves.&quot;  So, Vivienne resurrected me.  Sure, 93% isn't quite as good as 96%, but I learned a long time ago not to depend on resurrections.  I still believe that if I can get a resurrection, that's great.  If not, oh well.  It's just not that big of a deal.<br>
<br>
Was Kanina wrong for refusing to resurrect me?  Not in the slightest.<br>
<br>
You see, there are many different types of people here.  And there are many different styles of play.  Do not begrudge anyone because their style is different from yours.  Find friends with whom your style meshes.<br>
