  <p>~Wolf/Ssakas/Jr/Whatever</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sajuiil>Sajuiil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/03 12:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Labeling &quot;Evil&quot; and &quot;Good&quot;</span><hr size=1> All I have to add to this &quot;good&quot; and &quot;evil&quot; dead horse is that strict rules REALLY limit the Role-play experience everyone seems to value so much by:<br>
<br>
A) In a good fantasy &quot;good&quot; and &quot;evil&quot; constantly interact with each other. And although I completely agree with Shintou, dueling your friends playing your toon's counterparts is a hell of a lot of fun, its not enough. I, personally,  get a bigger kick picking on both &quot;good&quot; and &quot;evil&quot; (my toon is neutral) while grouping, than limiting my  interaction to my friends. You have to remember: without &quot;good&quot; there is no &quot;evil&quot; and vice versa. If one cannot live without the other, then why artificially insert those boundaries?<br>
<br>
B) If my woodelf rogue (who I don't even RP as a woodelf) kills the guards in Felwithe, is he still considered good? If eventually his faction at the Third Gate is better than in Kelethin, is he not evil enough? Cannot a monk be corrupted? Cannot a knight of shadows seduce a paladin with his dark powers? Cannot a druid be kidnapped at birth and instilled with hate while still being trained in the art of a druid ? (And yes, there are evil druids, plenty of fantasy books have entertained the idea). I have to agree that characters should be judged by actions not starting color of the toon.<br>
<br>
C) To add to point A). Yes, big/strong and/or well known guilds have a possibility to arrange events to play out the battles of &quot;good&quot; vs. &quot;evil&quot;. But what about the rest of us, struggling not only to find good groups and raids, but good RP opportunities? What better way to RP than in groups during the down time. I know, not everyone likes this idea (its a personal choice), but why keep your guildmates and give them grief and flat out prohibit them from grouping with the opposing force? If everyone cries &quot;let us RP the way we want&quot; does that mean that at the same time you will refuse to guild with people who don't RP EXACTLY the same as you?<br>
<br>
And finally, just a word about rezzing. I think its ridiculous to refuse a rez on the &quot;good&quot; vs. &quot;evil&quot; basis. For fuckmitten's sake (hehe.. just had to stick at least one cuss in ... this is Soapbox after all), step out of character for 10 sec it takes to cast a rez and help your fellow gamer avoid losing xp. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://sajuiil.4t.com/SajSig7.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 441<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/03 12:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Labeling &quot;Evil&quot; and &quot;Good&quot;</span><hr size=1> In my time on FV,I've refused at least five rez attempts by clerics.<br>
