<br>
I do think it's shallow of dark elves to run around calling themselves evil.  If they believed they were evil, they would kill themselves, unless, again, they were nuts.  What a Dark Elf does is what they consider to be good and righteous, so why don't they call it that?  If they call themselves evil, are they not, in essence, agreeing with the views of their enemies, the Koada'Dal and friends?  This is the basis of the &quot;Iksar Aren't Evil&quot; argument - An Iksar may be seen as evil by its enemies, but it certainly doesn't consider itself so, and neither should any creature that's sentient enough to consider such things.  So, I've just always thought of the Dark Elves skipping about screaming about how dark and evil they are as EQ's equivalent to the kid who calls himself a rebel because he owns a Godsmack CD. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taerinblackmaul>Taerin Blackmaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kaladim Cutie</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/03 12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hm</span><hr size=1> *as Tich finishes speaking, Taerin grabs him by the ear, drags him off and gives him a stern lecture* <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://209.167.100.172/files/sig/taerin3.jpg "/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lady of the House</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
