<br>
As long as your decisions are based on your character and role-played with panache, *I* have no problem with them, at least. Properly constructed characters are, I think, individuals, not stereotypes.<br>
<br>
The issue of perception that Kelisk raises is a good one, though I should note that those who favor moral determinism will recognize that they're assigned to &quot;evil,&quot; as it were, and won't have any problem claiming that and reveling in it. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.realitywerks.com/hosted-images/elludensig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
